          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1685529997837-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1685529997837-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>five-spice mix</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> in a medium bowl with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>five-spice marinade</strong></p><p>After the duck has been in the oven for 15 min, top with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>five-spice marinade </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and return the tray to the oven for a further 15 min or until golden and crispy – this is your <strong>five-spice roasted duck</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1685530001631-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
